/svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 06, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104akc1665702925834.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/akc1665702925834.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/akc1665702925834.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"akc1665702925834\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Databases\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface recognizes two kinds of database management systems—those that can manage individual fields within records (field-level DBMS) and those that manage records or files (record-level DBMS).\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"akc1665702925834__section_w2505ab1b5b1_w2506ab1b5_w2507ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d402943e51\">\n            \n Field-Level Databases\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"akc1665702925834__p_d46889e1_d46890e1_d46891e1\">A field-level DBMS stores fields as columns within a\n            table, and maintains information about the field length and storage format of each\n            field. Examples of field-level DBMSs are Sybase, Oracle, and Informix.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"akc1665702925834__p_d46892e1_d46893e1_d46894e1\">Most field-level DBMSs support both a DDL and a DML. The DDL allows database objects to be defined or described. The DML, which is sometimes called a query language, allows database objects to be manipulated or processed. For many field-level DBMSs, the DML is SQL, so the term SQL-like DBMS is sometimes used to describe a field-level DBMS.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"akc1665702925834__p_d46895e1_d46896e1_d46897e1\">Most, but not all, field-level DBMSs are relational. A Relational Database Management System (RDBMS) stores and retrieves data according to the relational data model. Not every field-level DBMS is relational, but every RDBMS is a field-level database.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"akc1665702925834__section_w2508ab1b5b3_w2509ab1b5_w2510ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d402943e66\">\n            \n Record-Level Databases\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"akc1665702925834__p_d46901e1_d46902e1_d46903e1\">A record-level DBMS is a relatively simple type of DBMS that stores and retrieves data in the form of records. With the possible exception of fields within indexes, it does not support the concept of fields. Access techniques are based on the physical data structures. Records can be retrieved by their position in the file and by indexes. The majority of record-level DBMSs do not support a DDL or a DML.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525733\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525733\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Databases Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 06, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Databases Uniface recognizes two kinds of database management systems—those that can manage individual fields within records (field-level DBMS) and those that manage records or files (record-level DBMS). Field-Level Databases A field-level DBMS stores fields as columns within a table, and maintains information about the field length and storage format of each field. Examples of field-level DBMSs are Sybase, Oracle, and Informix. Most field-level DBMSs support both a DDL and a DML. The DDL allows database objects to be defined or described. The DML, which is sometimes called a query language, allows database objects to be manipulated or processed. For many field-level DBMSs, the DML is SQL, so the term SQL-like DBMS is sometimes used to describe a field-level DBMS. Most, but not all, field-level DBMSs are relational. A Relational Database Management System (RDBMS) stores and retrieves data according to the relational data model. Not every field-level DBMS is relational, but every RDBMS is a field-level database. Record-Level Databases A record-level DBMS is a relatively simple type of DBMS that stores and retrieves data in the form of records. With the possible exception of fields within indexes, it does not support the concept of fields. Access techniques are based on the physical data structures. Records can be retrieved by their position in the file and by indexes. The majority of record-level DBMSs do not support a DDL or a DML. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}